$$b_1\le b_2\le\cdots\le b_k.$$

If $k$ is odd, rewrite its alternating sum as

$$b_1+(b_3-b_2)+(b_5-b_4)+\cdots+(b_k-b_{k-1}).$$

Every parenthesized difference is non-negative and $b_1>0$, so this sum is strictly positive. It cannot be zero.

